<h2> September 15, 2024 </h2>
A commission set up by the South Korean government has revealed that thousands of 
mothers were forced to give up their children for adoption abroad. Around 200,000 children, 
conceived by poor parents, especially single mothers, in government-funded welfare 
centres were adopted in nations like Australia, Denmark and the United States since the 1950s.<br>
Source: https://www.wionews.com/world/south-korean-mothers-were-falsely-declared-unfit-200000-babies-sent-abroad-for-adoption-757527<br>

